{{Quote|We've taken over this played out ''magma smelting plant''&hellip;|[[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]], to [[Lando Calrissian/Legends|Lando Calrissian]]|<ref name="SW50" />}}
'''Golrath Station''' was an abandoned [[Magma/Legends|magma]] smelting plant located in the mouth of a [[Volcano/Legends|volcano]] on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Golrath/Legends|Golrath]]. In [[3 ABY/Legends|3 ABY]], it briefly served as a [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] base after the Rebels' [[Battle of Hoth/Legends|defeat]] at [[Hoth/Legends|Hoth]] and the abandonment of [[Echo Base/Legends|Echo Base]]. The Rebels destroyed Golrath Station not long after their departure, after learning that the planet's bedrock had the ability to play back images that occurred nearby, potentially putting secrets at risk.

==Description==
{{Quote|Its walls must hold a living record of everything we did there&mdash;from visualizations of charts, to the coordinates for reaching ''Arbra''!|[[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]]|<ref name="SW65" />}}
A large [[Force field/Legends|force field]] dome protected the entire station from extreme thermal [[Temperature/Legends|temperatures]] and the rivers of [[Magma/Legends|lava]] that would rise up on the [[Volcano/Legends|volcano's]] perimeter from time to time. The bedrock that comprised the station's foundations harbored several strange characteristics. When heated, the mineral compounds absorbed ambient light rays, but when it cooled, it released those rays, playing them back; essentially, a natural [[Hologram/Legends|hologram]].<ref name="SW65" />

==History==
{{Quote|I know this installation was once a temporary Rebel base, Leftenant, but why is it important now?''"<br />"''It ''isn't'', Sergeant Malka. It was unimportant even when reported some time ago by a special agent planted in the Rebellion.|[[Sergeant/Legends|Sergeant]] [[Malka]] and Lieutenant Mils Giel|<ref name="SW65" />}}
Shortly after the [[Battle of Hoth/Legends|Battle of Hoth]], the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] maintained a temporary base of operations on [[Golrath/Legends|Golrath]].<ref name="SW50" /> They used the base as a makeshift training facility, but due to the cooling of the magma supply, they abandoned the hostile region to settle on the more temperate [[Planet/Legends|world]] of [[Arbra/Legends|Arbra]].<ref name="SW65" />

[[File:GolrathStation.png|thumb|left|235px|Golrath Station being searched by Imperial forces]]
[[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] forces learned of the abandoned station's existence and [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]] sent [[Lieutenant/Legends|Lieutenant]] [[Mils Giel]] there to supervise a survey team in the hopes of uncovering information concerning the Alliance. During his occupation, he discovered several holograms projected from the bedrock foundations detailing Rebel training sequences. He immediately transmitted a communiqué to Darth Vader describing what he had learned.<ref name="SW65" />

Meanwhile, [[Princess/Legends|Princess]] [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]] likewise learned about their old station's holographic capabilities. Aware that Golrath Station was now under Imperial control, she personally led a strike team to the planet's surface to [[Raid on Golrath Station|destroy]] any past evidence of their existence. Giel and Princess Leia faced one another inside the plant's reactor core chamber. Giel activated the overload circuits hoping that the destruction of the base might also kill Princess Leia. Both Leia and Giel managed to escape before the reactor core exploded, destroying the station.<ref name="SW65" />

==Behind the scenes==
Golrath Station was a setting of two issues of the original [[Star Wars (1977)|Marvel ''Star Wars'' comic run]], written by [[Archie Goodwin]]<ref name="SW50" /> and [[David Michelinie]],<ref name="SW65" /> and illustrated by [[Al Williamson]]<ref name="SW50" /> and [[Tom Palmer]].<ref name="SW65" />

